.TH "pdr_handle_alloc" 9 "pdr_handle_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pdr_handle_alloc \- initialize the PDR client handle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct pdr_handle *" pdr_handle_alloc
.BI "(void (*status)(int state, char *service_path, void *priv) "  ","
.BI "void *priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "status" 12
function to be called on PD state change
.IP "priv" 12
handle for client's use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initializes the PDR client handle to allow for tracking/restart of PDs.
.SH "RETURN"
pdr_handle object on success, ERR_PTR on failure.
